          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Currently, there is no widely approved routine screening test for HPV in men, analogous to the Pap smear or HPV test used for cervical screening. Diagnosis usually occurs when a symptom, such as a genital wart or a suspicious lump in the throat or anal region, appears."
        }
